name: gccsa_g13a_lang_spoken_at_home_by_profic_by_sex_census_2016
title: GCCSA-G13a Language Spoken at Home by Proficiency in Spoken Eng by Sex-Census 2016

legal.licenceType: Creative Commons Attribution 2.5 Australia (CC BY 2.5 AU)

keyword: english proficiency,sex,census,2016,gcp,g13a,language,gccsa,language spoken at home,general community profile
abstract:
GCCSA based data for Language Spoken at Home by Proficiency in Spoken English by Sex, in General Community Profile (GCP), 2016 Census. Count of persons. The list of languages consists of the most common Language Spoken at Home responses reported in the 2011 Census. G13 is broken up into 4 sections (G13a - G13d), this section contains 'Males Speaks English only' - 'Males Speaks Southeast Asian Austronesian Languages Other And speaks English Very well or well'.The data is by GCCSA 2016 boundaries. Periodicity: 5-Yearly.
Note: There are small random adjustments made to all cell values to protect the confidentiality of data. These adjustments may cause the sum of rows or columns to differ by small amounts from table totals.
For more information visit the data source: http://www.abs.gov.au/census.
